<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="74" type="macn">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="74">MACN.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
In the Burmeister collection there are two specimens that apparently belong to the type-series: a male specimen with no label pinned on it; it is in good condition; a female specimen with a green label with the inscription &quot;Buen[os] Aires,&quot; which is in quite good condition (Fig. 14). The habitus and scale of the two specimens correspond to the original description and they are associated with a square label on the box that reads &quot;Kinkelini Burm[eister] Buen[os] Air[es].&quot; Therefore, we assume they are syntypes. We hereby designate the female specimen as lectotype in [MACN] with a red label with the inscription &quot;Lectotype ♀ 
<taxonomicName authority="Hübner, 1820" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ecpantheria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ecpantheria kinkelini" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinkelini">Ecpantheria kinkelini</taxonomicName>
Burmeister designated by Beccacece, Vincent &amp; Navarro.&quot; The male specimen is designated as a paralectotype.
</paragraph>
